				On this note, allow me to personally recommend AutoDuel circa 1985 on the Commodore 64. Although not online, it is an RPG to be reckoned with. Harrowing in its stark minimalism, it is still my favorite. Reminiscent of riding some god-forsaken banana-seat bicycle across a country club golf course at midnight; the greenskeepers in pursuit drunk behind the wheels of gas-powered golf carts battered by tree trunks and the bones of small animals.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
