			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				You know what bugs me the absolute most about EverQuest players? The simple fact that they believe that EverQuest is the center of the universe. <BR>
<BR>
Look at some of these posts. Immediately compare it to EverQuest even though the game is 100% different. EverQuest copied from several other MUDs; it's a documented fact that EverQuest is nothing but bits and pieces of the greatest MUDs of all time. Ask anyone who has played online games since the Internet came into being. And no, AOL does NOT count.<BR>
<BR>
EverQuest is not all there is out there. There are other games that people enjoy more, because they don't appreciate the &quot;cash cow&quot; attitude that Verant has taken with this so-called online entertainment they plug as EverQuest. Verant is milking this cow for all it's worth, which about two cents, in my humble opinion.<BR>
<BR>
The game was fun for a while, but it's nothing but a full-time job after you hit level 50 and try to get to 60. Hell, I still have a 56 cleric. I log on every once in a while to talk to my friends, but I can't even rejoin my old &quot;uber&quot; guild, because they think that a level 56 cleric is a newbie. What the HELL is with that? The EverQuester attitude is annoying to say the least.
				</font>
			</td>

